---
title: Sweet Bourbon Cheddar Burgers with Potato Wedges & Garlic Aioli
description: We love an artisanal spin, and this burger seasoned with a smoky and savory-sweet bourbon spice rub elevates a classic to bold new heights. Melt cheddar over those juicy seared patties, then layer with tomato, ketchup, and garlic aioli between toasted buns, and serve with oven-roasted potato wedges and even more garlic aioli for dipping.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65f9c371c9eee2bcbf31fd7c-50b1c549.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65f9c371c9eee2bcbf31fd7c.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 1090 kcal
  fat: 70 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1720 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-bourbon-cheddar-burgers-65f9c371c9eee2bcbf31fd7c
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While potatoes cook, peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into
rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine garlic and @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}. Taste and season with salt
and pepper if desired.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce} and
@brown sugar bourbon seasoning{10.8%g}.

Form mixture into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider than a
burger bun.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and
cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last minute of cooking, top patties with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}; cover pan to
melt.

While patties cook, halve @potato bun{2} and toast until golden.

Spread cut sides of bottom buns with as much garlic aioli as you like. Spread a thin
layer of @ketchup{1%unit} onto cut sides of top buns. Fill with patties and tomato.

Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve with any remaining garlic aioli
on the side for dipping.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.